# {{CONSUMER_NAME}} — Agent Contract

This is the rulebook every Claude session in this repo obeys. It is
templated from `simodelne/pgas`'s `qc/AGENT_CONTRACT.md` and
`simodelne/pgas-rag`'s `qc/AGENT_CONTRACT.md`. Local additions are
welcome; deletions of the load-bearing sections below are not.

## The five irreducible rules

1. **`@simodelne/pgas-*` packages are upstream and read-only.** Never
   modify any file under `node_modules/@simodelne/pgas-*/`. If you
   find a bug there, file Channel 4 on `simodelne/pgas` (see
   CLAUDE.md "pgas ⇄ consumer communication protocol").

2. **The PGAS engine handles LLM-output governance.** Don't patch
   around LLM behavior in handler code. If a prompt misbehaves, fix
   the prompt, the spec, or the action description — not the handler.

3. **No silent failures.** If a behavior breaks, surface it. Per
   HANDOVER Rule 3 inherited from pgas: a swallowed error is a
   bug-shipping pattern.

4. **Data-driven debugging.** Per the user-global rule in
   `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`: when asked "why did X fail?", cite the
   observation, mark inferences as inferences, flag missing data, say
   "I don't know" when data is absent. Real cycles have been lost to
   "probably X" answers framed as confident root causes.

5. **No bypassing pre-commit hooks.** Use the staged-validation gates
   the scaffold installs (`pgas:spec-validate`, etc.). Emergency
   `--no-verify` bypasses are logged in git history and audited.

## Sub-agent contract

Per CLAUDE.md "Agent behavior — orchestrator role":

- **Orchestrator** (main Claude session): defines scope, dispatches
  briefs, reviews returned PRs, validates CI green, merges or rejects.
  Does not write code directly except for pure GH metadata.
- **Sub-agent** (Agent-tool dispatched): writes code, opens a PR,
  returns a report. Never self-merges.
- **Curator** (human): final veto on behavioral surfaces via CODEOWNERS.

Every sub-agent brief includes the classifier-denial rule verbatim
(see CLAUDE.md).

## FM-closure gates (pgas#253)

The plugin-scaffolded `programs/` and `server/` tree closes the five
failure modes by construction. The pre-commit hook + CI run:

- `/pgas:spec-validate` — every staged `*spec.yml`
- `/pgas:mode-entry-lint` — every staged `*spec.yml`
- `/pgas:5-fm-audit` — on every PR opened against `main`

A FAIL on any of these blocks the commit / PR merge.

## Architecture doc

Per `simodelne/pgas`/CONSUMER-VERSIONING-CONTRACT.md, every minor or
major version cut ships `audit/ARCHITECTURE-{{CONSUMER_NAME}}-v<X.Y.0>.md`.
Generate it with `/pgas:architecture-doc`. The post-tool-use hook
nudges on `npm publish` of a `.0` version.

## Governance-locked parameters

(Only applies if `{{GOVERNANCE_LOCKS}} == true`.) Any change to
`governance/approved_parameters.json` requires an `EVAL_LEDGER.md`
entry with paper-citation + effect-size evidence. The pre-commit
hook blocks otherwise (when wired in Phase 4+).
